<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUPLE FOUND SHOT TO DEATH; TODDLER CRITICALLY WOUNDED; 
</P>
<P>
SLAYINGS: POLICE CALL INCIDENT A MURDER-SUICIDE. HUSBAND AND WIFE REPORTEDLY 
HAD ARGUED FREQUENTLY OVER HIS EXTRAMARITAL AFFAIR. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN H. LEE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A couple who police said spent more than a year arguing frequently over the 
husband's continuing extramarital affair, were found shot to death in their 
Hollywood apartment Tuesday. Their 16-month-old son, wounded in the head, lay 
between them on their bed. 
</P>
<P>
The baby, Anthony Rodriguez, was reported in critical condition at Childrens 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles police said the incident appeared to be the third murder-suicide 
since May involving a couple in Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
Relatives found Leticia Peralta, 29, and Hector Rodriguez, 31, in their 
one-bedroom apartment in the 1800 block of North Kingsley Drive. A 
small-caliber automatic pistol was found near Peralta, said Hollywood Division 
Lt. Bob Ruchhoft. Peralta, Rodriguez and the baby apparently had each been shot 
once in the head, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Relatives of Rodriguez told investigators that Peralta became distraught last 
year when she learned that her husband was seeing another woman. Rodriguez, who 
worked as a janitor, refused to end the relationship and he and Peralta argued 
frequently, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Peralta also began threatening to kill her husband, said Luis Romero, 25, who 
identified himself as a close friend of Rodriguez. 
</P>
<P>
"He was saying he was going to leave his wife," Romero said of Rodriguez, who 
immigrated to the United States 11 years ago from Guatemala. "When she 
(Peralta) was angry, she said she would kill Hector. He used to joke about it." 
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez and Peralta, who worked as a housekeeper, had been married for about 
18 months, Romero said. 
</P>
<P>
In May, a man shot and killed his estranged wife and a daughter, wounded a 
second daughter, then killed himself in an apartment on Ardmore Avenue. In 
August, a few blocks away from the scene of Tuesday's shooting, a butcher, who 
was reportedly consumed by jealousy, fatally stabbed the woman he lived with, 
then shot to death his three children before killing himself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
