improvement in oil and gas, natural gas transmission, agribusiness and coal 
operations. The figures also included an after-tax charge of $16 million 
associated with the previously announced settlement in the Wyoming Tight Sands 
litigation, partially offset by an after-tax gain of $8 million from the sale 
of domestic gas properties. A net loss of $2 million was recorded due to the 
early retirement of debt, which was partially offset by a federal income tax 
benefit. 
