<TEXT>
<P>
McDonnell Douglas Layoffs Begin: McDonnell Douglas has begun laying off 1,000 
to 1,200 workers at its Long Beach and Torrance aircraft plants, part of a 
previously disclosed plan to eliminate 8,000 jobs at the two facilities this 
year. Employment at the two plants stood at 41,000 at the end of September. The 
company also disclosed plans to eliminate 1,500 jobs through attrition at the 
two facilities next year. 
</P>
