<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Withdrawals From S&amp;Ls Slow In May: The Office of Thrift Supervision 
reported that net withdrawals from the nation's savings and loans slowed to $7 
billion in May after soaring to a record $15.1 billion a month earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Depositors withdrew $3.2 billion from 2,471 solvent S&amp;Ls and another $3.8 
billion from the 312 failed institutions operated under government control. 
That compares to a net outflow in April of $9.6 billion at solvent institutions 
and $5.4 billion at government-run thrifts. The agency is about three months 
behind in its reporting of financial data. 
</P>
</TEXT>
