<HEADLINE>
<P>
PANEL RESTORES NEA GRANT RESTRICTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By The Washington Post 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A compromise that would have imposed no restrictions on the type of work funded 
by the National Endowment for the Arts was derailed in the Senate Tuesday when 
the Appropriations Committee reinstated a controversial list of forbidden 
subject matter. 
</P>
<P>
The committee also included language empowering the NEA to require grant 
recipients to sign a pledge of compliance with the content restrictions. The 
funding bill for fiscal year 1991 is expected to reach the Senate floor today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
