<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARRY C. (BUZZ) LORENZ JR.; RETIRED FINANCIAL ANALYST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harry C. (Buzz) Lorenz Jr., a retired financial analyst, has died at his North 
Hollywood home. He was 61. 
</P>
<P>
Lorenz died Sunday of complications of acquired immune deficiency syndrome, 
said his longtime companion, Robert E. Lampinen. 
</P>
<P>
Born April 26, 1929, in Wyandotte, Mich., he graduated in 1959 with a bachelor 
of science degree in accounting from Wayne State University in Detroit. He 
moved to California, where he settled in the San Fernando Valley. He worked as 
a financial analyst for various companies and retired in 1985 after 13 years as 
a senior cost analyst with Norris Industries in Vernon. Lorenz was also a 
member of the Valley Business Alliance, and enjoyed traveling and gourmet 
cooking. 
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his brother, Donald Lorenz of Santa Maria. 
</P>
<P>
A funeral, with burial to follow, is scheduled at 1:30 p.m. today at the Old 
North Church at Forest Lawn Memorial Park, 6300 Forest Lawn Drive, Hollywood 
Hills. Forest Lawn Mortuary is handling the arrangements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
