<HEADLINE>
<P>
1992 BREEDERS' CUP RACES WILL BE RUN AT SANTA ANITA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 1992 Breeders' Cup races will be run at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
Officials for the Oak Tree Racing Assn., which leases Santa Anita for the fall 
racing meeting, and the Breeders' Cup have come to terms after months of 
negotiations. 
</P>
<P>
The official announcement is expected after this year's Breeders' Cup, set for 
Belmont Park in New York on Oct. 27. 
</P>
<P>
Three of the first four Breeders' Cups were held in California, but the races 
haven't been run on the West Coast since 1987, when Hollywood Park was the 
site. Hollywood Park also had the first Breeders' Cup, in 1984, and the races 
were run at Santa Anita in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
Next year's Breeders' Cup is scheduled for Churchill Downs in Louisville. BILL 
CHRISTINE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
BREEDERS' CUP (HORSE RACE); HORSE RACES; SANTA ANITA RACE TRACK 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
