<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
DAMEWORTH RECORD TAKES A BEATING IN FRONTIER LEAGUE MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
George Barajas of Fillmore High shattered former Agoura standout Bryan 
Dameworth's course record at Soule Park in Ojai en route to a 16-second victory 
over Eric Renger of Calabasas in a Frontier League cross-country meet Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Barajas, who won in 15 minutes 37 seconds, and Renger both bettered Dameworth's 
1989 record of 16:19. 
</P>
<P>
Victor Hernandez of Fillmore was third and the Flashes, ranked first in the 
Southern Section Division IV coaches' poll, placed five runners among the top 
10 to win the team competition with 28 points. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Pierce d. Santa Monica, 15-2, 10-15, 15-7, 15-13 -- Carina Sailer and Marvette 
Williams each had 11 kills to lead unbeaten Pierce in a Western State 
Conference match at home. Amy Sodek had 27 assists and Lori Mertes had nine 
kills and five blocks for Pierce (11-0, 10-0 in WSC play). 
</P>
<P>
Redlands d. Cal Lutheran, 15-7, 15-7, 13-15, 15-11 -- Jennifer Wiley and 
Kristine Wegner each had seven kills in CLU's loss at home. The Regals dropped 
to 0-9; Redlands is 10-9. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' WATER POLO 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 20, St. Francis 2 -- Ron Scott, Andrew Jablon and Ryan Salceda each 
scored three goals for host Harvard (16-5, 4-0) in a San Fernando Valley League 
match. Goalie Antonio Gomez had 11 saves. 
</P>
<P>
Royal 16, Newbury Park 5 -- Chad Hood and Jack Kocur each scored four goals to 
pace Royal (14-3, 5-0) to its 46th consecutive Marmonte League victory in a 
match at Rancho Simi Pool in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks d. Westlake, 15-7, 15-6, 15-3 -- Amy Stone had 14 kills and 
Erikka Gulbranson added 12 to lead Thousand Oaks in a Marmonte League match at 
Westlake High. Jennifer Streltzoff had 34 assists and eight digs for Thousand 
Oaks (12-1, 9-0). 
</P>
<P>
Royal d. Camarillo, 15-6, 15-5, 15-3 -- Jennifer Hamilton had nine kills and 
four kill blocks and teammate Chantel Loo had 17 service points in a Marmonte 
League win for host Royal (10-1, 1-1). 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame d. St. Paul, 15-5,1 5-4, 15-11 -- Mary Strong and Phyliss Francis 
each had seven kills for visiting Notre Dame (9-2, 5-0) in a Mission League 
match. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark d. La Reina, 15-13, 15-2, 7-15, 15-2 -- Courtney Forman had 13 kills 
for Moorpark (9-0, 5-0) in Tri-Valley league match at La Reina (10-1, 4-1). 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth d. Cleveland 15-5, 15-4, 15-5 -- Marcia Gekhtman had eight kills and 
Lisa Koven and Jody Paperno each had seven for Chatsworth (8-0, 4-0) in a 
Northwest Valley Conference match at home. 
</P>
<P>
Burroughs d. Hart, 15-4, 15-4, 15-8 -- Jennifer Wagner had 16 kills and Carmen 
Gutierrez added eight to help the Indians (12-1, 5-0) defeat Hart in a Foothill 
League match at Burroughs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
