<P>
2 WOUNDED ON HARBOR FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men working on their disabled truck along a freeway shoulder in Los Angeles 
were shot and wounded by suspected gang members who pulled up and asked the 
victims if they belonged to a rival gang, authorities said today. 
</P>
<P>
The shooting occurred as the men, both from San Pedro, worked on their disabled 
pickup on the southbound Harbor Freeway near Channel Street late Tuesday, Sgt. 
Tony Rosa said. 
</P>
<P>
Gerald Wells and his cousin, Monet Williams, both 24, were taken to County 
Harbor-UCLA Medical Center, where both were in serious condition with gunshot 
wounds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
