<P>
WOMAN SAYS PRIEST SEDUCED HER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former church secretary wants $11 million from the Roman Catholic Church 
because a priest allegedly seduced her during counseling sessions and fathered 
her child. 
</P>
<P>
Debbie McCorvey, 34, alleges that Fernando Noe Guzman, formerly a priest at Our 
Lady of Fatima Church in Galena Park, engaged in professional malpractice and 
deceit by inducing her to have sex. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuit claims diocese officials knew of a pattern of sexual misconduct by 
Guzman, knew he had sexual relations with a minor when he was assigned to a 
church in Navasota and knew he fathered two illegitimate children while working 
as a priest in Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
McCorvey claims Guzman assured her their sexual relationship made them "one 
with God." 
</P>
<P>
McCorvey was fired from her church job in 1987, and Guzman also left the church 
that year. 
</P>
