<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAGIC MOOSE SETS RECORD AT LOS AL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Magic Moose put in a career effort Tuesday night in taking the $20,000 U.S. 
Harness Writers Trot feature by 3 1/4 lengths over his entrymate, Dear Miss. 
</P>
<P>
Trained by Pete Foley and driven by Ross Croghan, Magic Moose traversed his 
victorious mile in a lifetime best 1:56 4/5. 
</P>
<P>
That mile not only broke his track record for aged trotting geldings, it made 
him the fastest trotter in Los Alamitos history. 
</P>
<P>
Magic Moose tracked the pace-setting BH Dynamite down the backstretch, then was 
able to clear after a fast 1:27 1/4 three-quarters. 
</P>
<P>
Magic Moose and Dear Miss were the second favorites in the wagering and paid 
$10.60 to win. 
</P>
<P>
Dear Miss picked up the place money over Nothing Ventured, who had to settle 
for the show and an end to his 10-race winning streak. 
</P>
</TEXT>
